    """
    The solution consists of solving a system of linear equations.
    The system is represented by the following equation:
    $$
    z_i - z_i - \cdots = (z_1 + 2 * z_2 + \cdots + 2 * z_{n-1}) * a_i - n
    $$
    where $a_i$ is the number of swords of the $i$-th type, $z_i$ is the number of swords of the $i$-th type taken by the $i$-th person, and $z_1, z_2, \dots, z_{n-1}$ are the values of $z_1, z_2, \dots, z_{n-1}$ which have not been taken yet.

    The solution is obtained by solving this system of linear equations and using the theorem of least square to solve for $z_i$.
    """
    n, *a = map(int, stdin.split())
    b = [sum(a) - i for i in a]
    res = np.linalg.lstsq(np.vstack((np.identity(n), -np.identity(n))), b, rcond=None)[0]
    return''.join(map(str, res[-1:]))
